      "text": "A social [[charter]] is one of the convivial [[constituting tools]] of [[Peer Governance in Commons]]. It is \"a declaration of intent to hold a commons in trust for its beneficiaries.\", as James Quilligan ([http://www.kosmosjournal.org/contributor/james-bernard-quilligan/ html]) put it. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "3b89d1dc1e01b2d6",
      "text": "A Social Charter for the Commons is not a Business Charter for Social Responsibility ([http://socialvaluecommissioning.org/2016/10/20/the-birmingham-business-charter-for-social-responsibility/ html]) in that it provides the institutional basis for the management and protection of a [[commons]] or a shared resource governed by the commoners themselves. "
    },
