      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "0983f4a96bf54eac",
        "text": "A social [[charter]] is \"a declaration of intent to hold a commons in trust for its beneficiaries.\" (James Quilligan). It provides the institutional basis for the management and protection of a [[commons]] or a shared resource. Creating a social charter requires the support and involvement of people across a region or community of interest who depend on a shared resource for their livelihood and welfare. It can be developed for a single commons or for overlapping commons."
